    "body": "The current steps are:\r\n\r\n## Building the Prod Web UI Bundle\r\n\r\nMake sure you have node < v17 installed (we use v15). Then:\r\n\r\n```\r\ngit clone git@github.com:prysmaticlabs/prysm-web-ui && cd prysm-web-ui\r\nnpm install\r\nnpm run build:prod\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis will build the web UI to the `dist/` folder.\r\n\r\n## Creating the Gzipped Release Asset with Sha\r\n\r\nThen, we gzip the built bundle with\r\n```\r\ncd dist && tar -czvf ~/Desktop/prysm-web-ui.tar.gz .\r\n```\r\nWe then create a shasum256 for the file gzipped file\r\n```\r\ncd ~/Desktop && shasum -a 256 prysm-web-ui.tar.gz > ~/Desktop/prysm-web-ui.tar.gz.shasum256\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Tag a Web UI Release\r\n\r\nWe then tag a release on Github in the web UI repository and upload both assets (gzipped and shasum file)\r\n\r\n## Bake the New Web UI Release into the Prysm Repo\r\n\r\nThen, we go into the Prysm repository, and perform the following steps:\r\n\r\nIn the WORKSPACE file, find the line with:\r\n```\r\nhttp_archive(\r\n    name = \"prysm_web_ui\",\r\n    build_file_content = \"\"\"\r\nfilegroup(\r\n    name = \"site\",\r\n    srcs = glob([\"**/*\"]),\r\n    visibility = [\"//visibility:public\"],\r\n)\r\n\"\"\",\r\n    sha256 = \"f196fe4367c2d2d01d36565c0dc6eecfa4f03adba1fc03a61d62953fce606e1f\",\r\n    urls = [\r\n        \"https://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm-web-ui/releases/download/v1.0.2/prysm-web-ui.tar.gz\",\r\n    ],\r\n)\r\n```\r\nand update the version in the URL as well as the sha256 with the new values.\r\n\r\nThen, try to build the site data\r\n```\r\nbazel build //validator/web:site_data\r\n```\r\n\r\nCopy the built site data from the bazel folders into the Prysm repo\r\n```\r\ncp bazel-bin/validator/web/site_data.go ./validator/web/site_data.go\r\n```\r\n\r\nFormat the file:\r\n```\r\ngofmt -w -s ./validator/web/site_data.go\r\n```\r\nCreate a pull request in the Prysm repo with your changes",
